Fire those LEG & BUTT🔥 - this one is a MUST try if you still at home or no access to weights room. SAVE & TAG your bff 👯‍♀️ - don't be selfish LMAO 😏
.
OKAY, now who else is READY to kick some a** and start the week strong?! 🙋🏻‍♀️ If you are interested in workouts that are EFFECTIVE (no cookie butter plan or magic tricks 🙄 like we can see on the internet) Email me or click link in bio. I only work with the serious ones!
.
Grab your bands and 2 gallon of water, if you have that perfect, if you don't grab something heavy from around!
.
Workout instructions:
.
No rest between exercises
60 sec rest after each rounds
There are 4 total. 
GW = Gallon water E/S= each side
.
1️⃣ GW BANDED PULSES SQUAT WALK - 10 steps total (get 2 low pulses at low squat)
2️⃣ RESISTED BAND 3/4 SUMO SQUATS - 10 total + 10 BANDED JUMPS
push backwards against the bands as you come up - squeeze you butt and abs - you will feel it a LOT
3️⃣ SINGLE LEG HAMMIE LYING CURL - 10 E/S do these slow & controlled, the hamstring and glutei should be fired up 
4️⃣ GW BANDED B-STANCE SQUAT SIDE LEG LIFT - 10 E/S (use a light to medium band - I did use the strongest and then It was too hard LOL.  its about form not else…)
Your bodyweight is on the fix leg, squat down, lift your leg up + squeeze your glutes as you come high. You can tap down the floor to help with balance.
5️⃣ SQUAT BAND SIDE TOE TAPS - 5 reps E/S
(3 taps = 1 rep, so repeat 5x and then move onto the other leg.
6️⃣ LYING SINGLE LEG HAMMIE CURL - 10E/L (husband didn’t do a very good job filming this sorry lol) - do these slow controlled, make sure to feel it in your hamstring!
7️⃣ LYING CURL - 10 leg together - Control those and squeeze at the top🔥
.

.

node.text:
Do 3 sets of 15 reps 30 sec rest

Workout description 
1. Start with the abs are they are the foundation of your body, on an decline bench, if you don’t have a ViRP, dumbbell or a bar will do the work too .
.
2. Follow by L-seat ring legs should be 😆 90° or above from the floor. Always keep control of your body. The challenge here is to move and maintain stability: HI SHOULDER MUSCLES! .
.
3. Reverse grip face pull: you fire up not only your back but your core and your Lower body by the isometric contraction...! Super efficient to get your back strong, defined and powerful shoulders!
.
4. Pyramidal deadlift, consists of increasing the weights as set go! Keep your core tight, back remains straight, eyes look in the same direction as your body move up and down (does it make sense? 😅) .
.
5. T bar squat, I do a sumo version  because I felt more comfortable that way. Find the best stance for yourself. Increase weight as well until the last 2-3 reps are difficult.... .
.

node.text:
Knock knock ✊… 

coming back in full force this coming weeks! If you missed me - comment a 🥳 and if you don’t - remind silent 😂 

Took a week off, focusing on myself and some majors priorities. Me. It’s not selfish. It’s vital. Nothing will work with an empty tank. 😚 There is this saying: you can’t love if you don’t love yourself first. You can’t give if you’re not ready to receive. 

One day something needs to click. To realize what’s important and what isn’t. The principal to learn to care for yourself first and not much of what others think of you. The matter to realize how far you have come. When things were such a mess you thought you will never recover.  Then you smile. You see the progress. You smile because you are truly proud of yourself for those accomplishments which can be emotional, physical or what is in the mind. Proud of yourself to fought the person you become. 

If this make sense please drop a heart ❤️☺️

node.text:
Gratitude moment 
Hope everyone had a wonderful Labor Day 🇺🇸yesterday. I was invited to the 1st official opening pool party 🎉 at the @hardrockstadium. You know where the famous hotel guitar is. It was awesome. 

I met a lot of great people, from promoter to my amazing FitWarriors. New ones and the ones who have been part of the foundation of who I became today. 😋 I’d like to say THANK YOU for being part of my journey. In the bad and in the good. So you know, I truly appreciate every single of you here who following me. 
How should or can I say: Fans? followers? Well, up to you. What I want you to remember is I care for you.

Don’t hesitate to say hi, I might not know who you are all but if I see you commenting most of the time or sharing/ tagging me a lot  to your stories, I have more chance to know you haha! Right? 😋 

For those I missed the world is small we will meet one day 💗 

What did you ended doing yesterday?

In case you’re feeling sh## today, here’s a reminder that it’s normal to fall apart. My heart hurts😔 and my emotions a mess. 

Thought I rather expose a real time post, so we remember that “influencers” and all the posed pics, matching themes/colors tones and inspirational 10ish characters, in an island with luxury cars parting and smiling, isn’t a reflection of a perfect life. 

There is no such thing as balance.  Life will forever be 5 pots boiling and only 4 lids cover. By balance, it means switching lids, turn off one stove. It’s ALWAYS a shuffling game. So cry. Be sad, mad, angry,… maybe all in once, then SWIM FORWARD & try to FIGURE IT OUT. 

Ps: this isn’t an AirFrance flight, you don’t need to announce your departure if you unfollow. 👍

HOW I EAT 👇 FAQ
"What do you think of xxxx Diet?"
"Do you track macros?"
"How many calories do you have daily?"
-
My diet and exercise philosophy is to do what is enjoyable - unless you’re preprin’ for a show. There is more than ONE way to reach a goal. What matters is results & what you can realistically stick to?
-
I don't follow any specific diet, I have a very specific idea of what to do and what works for me now. Honestly you should learn too (and on that I can help you 😉). it’s a process. There are some decent diets if you're the type that needs "rules".
•
🎯 My goal is to steadily continue burning fat while slightly building muscles and defined
•
📝 I generally don't track macros or count calories long term unless I want to be ready for a shoot or event. For my current goal & lifestyle I find it's not necessary nor sustainable to neurotically track every meal indefinitely.
•
🍗 Ideally I consume at least 1600 ish calories per day. I tried 2000 or + but for me it was “too much” I was putting a lot of muscles and fat too - you know that not used proteins are transformed by the body in fat right?
•
🥑 I naturally consume fat like, olives oil, coconut oil, nuts or peanut chocolate butter (those so yummy)
•
🥗 Ideally most meals include 1 serving of various non-starchy veggies in addition to daily green veggies 
•
🥔 I try my best to consume carbohydrates strategically - trying to consume the majority of my starchy/ high carbs allowance after my post workout meal and stick to low-impact high fiber carbs throughout my other meals.
•
🍪 I love cookies, chocolate, & pizza! I can occasionally eat one if I'm craving it and be good to go back to my normal healthy diet.
I do find if I have too many treats, I crave them more so I'm mindful of my sugar intake.
-
One diet style does not fit all! Can I get a "🙌" if you agree?!
What works for you? I want to hear about your diet & how it's going!👇.
As an online coach the biggest importance to me is that all my clients are fully satisfied and seeing the results they want to.
